{"agent_id":"claude","agent_seq":15,"timestamp":"2026-06-21T00:28:17.430068721Z","event":{"type":"IssueCreated","uuid":"cb37a1f4-6c6e-46f2-89bd-093247725de7","title":"Address Copilot review on PR #1175","description":"Steps to reproduce:\n1. \n\nExpected: \nActual: \n\nPR: docs: capture architectural knowledge (design-principles + Architecture-Internals)\nhttps://github.com/openwpm/OpenWPM/pull/1175\n\n## Unresolved Copilot review threads\n\n- `docs/design-principles.rst:71`\n\n  The worked example describes routing a JS instrumentation failure back to `BrowserManager` over the extension's privileged socket, but the current socket path is not an extension-to-`BrowserManager` failure channel: `BrowserManager` creates a `ClientSocket` that only sends messages, and the extension's `ListeningSocket` callback only receives Initialize/Finalize/visit-id messages. As written, this example can mislead contributors into relying on a channel that does not currently deliver failures back to `BrowserManager`; either describe the additional protocol that would be needed or use an existing failure-reporting path.\n\n---\n\nVERIFY each claim before acting — Copilot is fallible (it once flagged a valid os.getenv(key, default=...) as a bug). If real -> fix + resolve the thread. If wrong -> post a reasoned rebuttal + resolve. Builder -> the-hater -> done; never blindly apply.","priority":"high","created_by":"claude","display_id":62},"signed_by":"SHA256:s7/xSWzYQxlilryCkQ+87ei/Tb4h7UF7S3hGGeMOxBg","signature":"U1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgxYoY2+ykEqIdJITiF+QWTxSzAQrzXLyHaApd+5sgGJAAAAAPY3Jvc3NsaW5rLWV2ZW50AAAAAAAAAAZzaGE1MTIAAABTAAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAQPuq6JbNNq86GMJpO9smdO+BG3WQfK7c+etoWoqwdC6BXCaGMHenCABWNOb3hqGOBtqU04Qz13HiefDedKqmjQI="}
